he \u0026quot;halo\u0026quot; ring feature. LED lights are very bright, and use about half of the amperage of the stock lights (even less if you are dealing with high wattage halogens). \u0026nbsp;The advantages are long life, bright, white light, and the lower amperage unloads the electrical system so that you don\u0026#39;t need relays to save your headlight switch. The only slight modification you will have to do is bend one of the three indentations of the headlight bucket where the light sits in the bucket. \u0026nbsp;It is just a hair too big to fit as is. \u0026nbsp;I used a set of grips and then just picked the indentation that was the easiest to get to, and tweaked that about 1/32\u0026quot; until the light fit in snugly. \u0026nbsp;Takes just a minute and no special tools. \u0026nbsp; \u0026nbsp;Watch our video to get an idea of what they are like installed:\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ciframe allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ScNPM-TGtT0\" width=\"560\"\u003e\u003c/iframe\u003e\u003ciframe allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/sudjVTZbRps\" width=\"560\"\u003e\u003c/iframe\u003e\u003ciframe allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/e_8OpVsl4tM\" width=\"560\"\u003e\u003c/iframe\u003e\u003ciframe allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/2JYEFulYOg4\" width=\"560\"\u003e\u003c/iframe\u003e\u003ciframe allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/BK1gmqLUJRE\" width=\"560\"\u003e\u003c/iframe\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"44:[\"$\",\"div\",\"10798\",{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"className\":\"round